Creating spring application in Eclipse IDE
Go to File menu - New - project - Java Project. 
Write the project name e.g. firstspring - 
Finish. Now the java project is created.

There are mainly three jar files required to run this application

org.springframework.core-3.0.1.RELEASE-A
com.springsource.org.apache.commons.logging-1.1.1
org.springframework.beans-3.0.1.RELEASE-A

To run this example, you need to load only spring core jar files.

Right click on your project - Build Path - Add external archives 
- select all the required jar files - finish

